values: Well, I broke up with my girlfriend. Hoorah.
As of today, I am no longer single.

Well, Christmas is coming up soon. I already know what i'm getting

What i'm getting:
Lava Lamp (come on now, who doesn't like lava lamps?)
Digital Camera
Pink Floyd: The Wall (the DVD)
Gift card from my grandparents

I think theres something else I wanted as well, but I cant remember.
Well, I sold my Game Boy SP for $40. What did I buy with my money, you ask? Oh yeah.

Well shit. My mom got some e-mails from the government saying my and my mom's boyfriend have been going to like 30 illegal sites (mostl ikely music sites). Out of all the people, why me? Now I can't download music anymore.

EDIT: Nevermind, it was just spam mail.
Changed my LJ around a little bit again.
4 and a half day weekend. FUCK YEAH!

Here's something interesting I discovered a while back, but forgot about until recently. Look at this picture: now look at this site: The Charcoal Corral IT'S THE SAME PICTURE! I think we may have a mystery on our hands.

Well, i'm in my new room. I still don't have everything in here and organized, and some of my sister's stuff is still in here, but i'll worry about all that later. I'm still gonna get some more of my stuff in here tonight, but the rest of my sister's stuff has to stay in here until tomorrow.

Well, i'll be moving into the bigger bedroom this weekend, and getting my mom's bedroom set whenever she buys the one from her friend.

New bedroom: HELL FUCKING YES!
New bed and dresser: HELL FUCKING YES!



Edit: Meant to say CAN instead of CANT
Edit 2: Fuck it, got rid of the third one.

Oh, I forgot to mention that my friend DROPKICKED a door into some girl. Here's what happened: me and my friends were hangin out in the courtyard, and we were gonna go through side doors and walk around school (even though we weren't supposed to). Well, a couple girls were pushing against the doors so we couldn't get in. I tried running into it so it would open (it had one of those things you pushed to open the door). It didn't work, and my friend says he wants to try. Well, he runs and fucking DROPKICKS it and gets it open for a second. The girl was shocked, and a couple teachers came out and yelled at us, and my friend got in trouble.

Well, in a couple weeks i'll be moving out of my room and into my sister's room, which is twice the size of my room and was my room over a year ago (before i moved into the basement). My mom's buying a bedroom set from her friend, which means i'll be getting her Queen Size bed and her dresser (the one that's in the upstairs hallway). Whoo!
you havent lived until youve seen special ed kids doing woody woodpecker impersonations
bought a new cd yesterday. nirvana - nevermind
I have a lot of video games. I wonder how much I can get for them?
Gave my Livejournal color theme. Whaddya guys think?

I got a problem. I haven't had a girlfriend in over a year and a half. The only problem is that i'm shy and i'm a smartass. The only time i'm a smartass is when i'm in classes with my friends and i'm trying to be funny and make friends that way. Other times i'm shy. See, chicks don't like smartasses. If I stop being a smartass, then I probably won't make that many friends in school because i'm shy and I don't go outta my way to make friends.
Got a haircut last night. It's really short now.

It's been a while. Well, school's going great. Halloween is fastly approaching. I love the Hallowen season, almost as much as I love the Christmas season. I'm thinking about getting a haircut. As much as I like having longer hair, I look better and older with short hair.

Well, it's Tuesday. School starts tomorrow.

Fuck.

wow i havent updated this thing in a while

i got a new computer

my moms boyfriend got a new job

thats pretty much everything exciting thats happened recently

Man oh man, i'm gonna be selling a LOT at our yard sale this weekend. My portion includes, but is not limited to:

*my VHS tapes

*my cassettes

*a bunch of video games

*a couple of speakers

*TVs

*alarm clocks

*an Austin Powers thing that I won at an arcade years ago

*a keyboard and a mouse



I can't really remember what else i'm selling, but i promise you that its a LOT. Plus, whatever I don't sell gets sold on eBay, and I get to keep all the profits. Why am I selling all this stuff, you ask? Mainly because I need the money and the space.

Woohoo, I finally got my TV with the woodgrain finish back from my sister. I let her borrow it some time ago, and I got it back today. Since I don't feel like takin a pic of it, here's an old pic I took of it back in February:

A few things: 1)My mom and her boyfriend are back. 2) My TV's fucked up. All the channels are really fuzzy. So now i'm using a small TV that doesn't have a thing for cable (cause it broke off) and only an A/V thing to play my video games and shit, and I watch TV downstairs (which isn't that bad, cause the air conditioner's down there). My regular TV The TV i'm using now Size comparison 3) Posters look so cool when you put them on your windows. It's like they light up or something. My Nirvana poster, and directly below that: One of my Scarface posters
Well, turns out she was leaving today instead of tomorrow.

Well, my mom's leaving to go to Kentucky on my birthday for her boyfriend's court thing (he's there because of some child support thing with his ex-wife), but she's giving me some birthday money before she leaves, plus she's comin' back Thursday night (she hopes), and my party'll be on Saturday, so it's all good.

My birthday's in 6 days. Go me. I'm just askin' for money, so at the moment, this is what I want to buy:

1) A new T.V. My T.V. (a 28" I believe) is messed up because most of the channels are fuzzy. I'll probably just get a flat screen 13"

2) A new stand for the new T.V. I don't need a huge stand for a small T.V.

EDIT: Fuck it, i'll just using my computer as an alarm clock from now on.

3) Some C.D.s

4) A NES controller for the computer

5) An adaptor that allows me to play SNES games on my computer

And if I have any money leftover:

6) A flat monitor. I saw a really cheap one at Wal-Mart.

Hope everyone's havin' a great summer.
